</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[227,1437,879,1152]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
A bibliography including the synonymy of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1966" box="[910,1060,879,905]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monepidosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[910,1060,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Monepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was given in the revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1913" box="[227,414,914,940]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Porricondylinae">Porricondylinae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C." box="[456,784,914,940]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref9290" refString="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C. 2013. The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia Dipterologica Supplement 20: 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1966" box="[920,1070,914,940]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monepidosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[920,1070,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Monepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from each other using characters of the male gonocoxites, or more specifically, the processes at the ventroposterior gonocoxal margin, which vary in size, shape and position. There are two kinds of processes: the gonocoxal processes, which are outgrowths of the medial bridges, and the central processes, which are outgrowths of the ventral bridge (
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C." box="[616,928,1055,1081]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref9290" refString="Jaschhof M. &amp; Jaschhof C. 2013. The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia Dipterologica Supplement 20: 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013</bibRefCitation>
; this paper, 
<figureCitation box="[1066,1169,1055,1081]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[227,270,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[324,1306,795,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[306,1327,786,1955]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 10. Monepidosis heterocera sp. nov., Æ‹. A. Genitalia, ventral, holotype. B. Genitalia, ventral (paratype). C. Processes at ventroposterior gonocoxal margin, ventral, paratype. Scale lines: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3837783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3837783/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). Apart from genitalic structures, the morphology of male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1966" box="[665,815,1090,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monepidosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[665,815,1090,1116]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Monepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely uniform. Females and larvae of most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1966" box="[227,377,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Monepidosis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,377,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Monepidosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, including the species treated here, are unknown.
</paragraph>
